---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout seo={{
  title: 'Privacy & Data Handling',
  description: 'ZDR Chat is built on a zero-data-retention model. Your conversations, API keys, and settings stay in your browser — always.',
}}>
  <div class="container-main py-24">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <!-- Hero section -->
      <header class="mb-20">
        <div class="mx-auto mb-8 flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-emerald-500/10">
          <span class="text-3xl">🔐</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-center text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-5xl">
          Your Data. Your Browser. Your Rules.
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-center text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
          ZDR Chat was built around one conviction: <strong class="text-emerald-400">privacy isn't a feature, it's the foundation.</strong>
          Every design decision starts and ends with keeping your data in your hands.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- The Pledge -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-emerald-500/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-950/40 to-slate-900/40 p-8 sm:p-12">
          <h2 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest text-emerald-400 uppercase">The ZDR Pledge</h2>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 sm:text-3xl">
            Zero Data Retention. Zero Compromise.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
            We collect nothing. We store nothing. We log nothing. Your conversation history lives in your browser's
            IndexedDB. Your API key is stored locally. We run no servers, maintain no databases, and have no backend
            — the entire app is a static PWA deployed to Cloudflare Pages. When you close the tab, the connection
            to the world is gone. Your data remains in your browser, for your eyes only, until you choose to clear it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Data Flow -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 sm:text-3xl">Where Your Data Lives</h2>

        <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/40 p-6">
            <div class="mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-emerald-500/10">
              <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-emerald-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">Conversations</h3>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
              Every message lives in your browser's <strong class="text-slate-300">IndexedDB</strong>.
              Organized by conversation, searchable, exportable. Never copied anywhere else.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/40 p-6">
            <div class="mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-emerald-500/10">
              <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-emerald-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 7a2 2 0 012 2m4 0a6 6 0 01-7.743 5.743L11 17H9v2H7v2H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-2.586a1 1 0 01.293-.707l5.964-5.964A6 6 0 1121 9z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">Your API Key</h3>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
              Stored in <strong class="text-slate-300">localStorage</strong>. Read only when making a request.
              <em>We never see it — not even once.</em>
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/40 p-6">
            <div class="mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-emerald-500/10">
              <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-emerald-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10.325 4.317c.426-1.756 2.924-1.756 3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 002.573 1.066c1.543-.94 3.31.826 2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 001.066 2.573c1.756.426 1.756 2.924 0 3.35a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.066 2.573c.94 1.543-.826 3.31-2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.573 1.066c-.426 1.756-2.924 1.756-3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.573-1.066c-1.543.94-3.31-.826-2.37-2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.066-2.573c-1.756-.426-1.756-2.924 0-3.35a1.724 1.724 0 001.066-2.573c-.94-1.543.826-3.31 2.37-2.37.996.608 2.296.07 2.572-1.065z" />
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">Preferences</h3>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
              Theme, density mode, model sort — all in <strong class="text-slate-300">localStorage</strong>.
              Persistent across sessions, gone when you clear your data.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Data Flow Diagram -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 sm:text-3xl">The Only Data Flow</h2>
        <p class="mb-8 text-lg text-slate-400">
          There is exactly one network request in ZDR Chat: from your browser to OpenRouter. Nothing more.
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/30">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 divide-x divide-slate-700/50">
            <div class="p-6 text-center sm:p-8">
              <div class="mb-3 flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-2xl">🌐</span>
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Your Browser</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
                Key from localStorage<br />
                Messages from IndexedDB<br />
                Sent via HTTPS
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-center p-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-emerald-400">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3" />
                </svg>
                <span class="text-sm font-medium">HTTPS</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 text-center sm:p-8">
              <div class="mb-3 flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-2xl">🤖</span>
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider">OpenRouter</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
                Receives your request<br />
                Streams the response<br />
                <span class="text-emerald-400">ZDR enforced</span>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/50 px-6 py-4 text-center text-sm text-slate-500">
            ↳ No intermediate servers. No databases. No logging. No analytics.
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- What never happens -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 sm:text-3xl">What Never Happens</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 rounded-xl border border-red-900/30 bg-red-950/20 p-5">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-xl">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-100">No data collection</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">We don't collect, store, or transmit any usage data, analytics, or telemetry.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 rounded-xl border border-red-900/30 bg-red-950/20 p-5">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-xl">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-100">No accounts</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">No sign-up, no user IDs, no profiles. You don't exist in our database because there is no database.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 rounded-xl border border-red-900/30 bg-red-950/20 p-5">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-xl">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-100">No tracking scripts</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">Zero analytics, zero pixels, zero cookies. The page loads and that's it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 rounded-xl border border-red-900/30 bg-red-950/20 p-5">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-xl">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-100">No data selling</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">There's nothing to sell — we never have your data in the first place.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Clear Your Data -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 sm:text-3xl">Clearing Your Data</h2>
        <p class="mb-6 text-lg text-slate-400">
          Because everything is local, clearing your data is straightforward — and immediate.
        </p>
        <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/40 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
              <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-emerald-500/10 text-sm">1</span>
              In the App
            </h3>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
              Click the settings gear, select <strong class="text-slate-300">Clear All Data</strong>, confirm.
              Every conversation, your API key, and all preferences are gone instantly.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/40 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
              <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-emerald-500/10 text-sm">2</span>
              In Your Browser
            </h3>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
              Open DevTools → Application → Clear site data for <code class="text-emerald-300">app.zdr.chat</code>.
              Same result: everything gone, no traces anywhere.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- OpenRouter ZDR -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 sm:text-3xl">Enforcing ZDR at the Network Layer</h2>
        <p class="mb-6 text-lg text-slate-400">
          ZDR Chat sends <code class="text-emerald-300">X-ZDR: 1</code> with every request, but for full enforcement,
          configure your OpenRouter account:
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/40 p-5">
            <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-emerald-500/10 font-bold text-emerald-400">1</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">Enable ZDR at the account level</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-base text-slate-400">
                Visit <a href="https://openrouter.ai/settings/privacy" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">OpenRouter Privacy Settings</a>
                and switch on Zero Data Retention. This applies to all requests from your account by default.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/40 p-5">
            <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-emerald-500/10 font-bold text-emerald-400">2</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">Enable the ZDR guardrail</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-base text-slate-400">
                This prevents per-request settings from disabling ZDR. Think of it as a safety catch — if a client
                accidentally sends <code class="text-emerald-300">X-ZDR: 0</code>, the guardrail blocks it.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-8 text-base text-slate-500">
          With both enabled, every request is ZDR-guaranteed at the network layer. OpenRouter will not log your prompts,
          responses, or metadata — period.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Services -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 sm:text-3xl">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
          The only external service ZDR Chat connects to is <strong class="text-slate-100">OpenRouter</strong>.
          We use no analytics, no tracking scripts, no CDN fonts, and no external embeds.
          The site is deployed on Cloudflare Pages, which handles DNS and CDN routing
          — it does not process your application data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Final word -->
      <section>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-800/30 p-8 text-center sm:p-12">
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">
            Privacy isn't a policy — it's the product.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base text-slate-400">
            If you have questions, concerns, or ideas, reach out on{' '}
            <a href="https://github.com/khattaksd/zdrchat" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">GitHub</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>